Issues.Title: Animation of a 3D point over any 3D path in wpf
Issues.Body:
_This issue has been moved from [a ticket on Developer Community](https://developercommunity.visualstudio.com/content/idea/388994/animation-of-a-3d-point-over-any-3d-path-in-wpf.html)._ ---

Do you expect to support animation of a 3D point over any 3D path in wpf in the near future? Such a capability is very useful for engineering and scientific applications. One often needs to model deformation of bodies or galaxies etc defined by paths followed by vertices (of triangles used to model the body) often obtained by some computation.

Regards;

i.konuk

--- ### Original Comments #### Jane Wu [MSFT] on 11/22/2018, 04:43 PM:

Thank you for taking the time to provide your suggestion. We will do some preliminary checks to make sure we can proceed further. You will hear from us in about a week on our next steps.
Issues.RelatedDescription: Open issue "Animation of a 3D point over any 3D path in wpf" (#3453)

Issues.Title: CommandParameter evaluates CanExecute
Issues.Body:
_This issue has been moved from [a ticket on Developer Community](https://developercommunity.visualstudio.com/content/idea/361782/commandparameter-evaluates-canexecute.html)._ ---

Behavior concerning ButtonBase-Class:

Currently, only the ValueChangedCallback from the CommandProperty invokes the CanExecute-Method of the given Command. It would be highly useful, if also the ValueChangedCallback of the CommandParameterProperty would invoke CanExecute on the Command (if not null).

--- ### Original Comments #### Fiona Niu[MSFT] on 10/19/2018, 05:51 PM:

Thank you for taking the time to provide your suggestion. We will do some preliminary checks to make sure we can proceed further. You will hear from us in about a week on our next steps.
Issues.RelatedDescription: Open issue "CommandParameter evaluates CanExecute" (#3452)

https://github.com/dotnet/wpf/blob/be89bbfaded6ad3f0f4143bf1a8dd075a5789715/global.json#L24

.NET 5 still using intellisense data from .NET Core 3.0 docs. This needs to be updated to use .NET 5 docs based data.

@dotnet/dotnet-winforms - [dotnet/winforms](https://github.com/dotnet/winforms) also has this bug I think. 

[winforms/global.json@L22 in 0416d4](https://github.com/dotnet/winforms/blob/0416d4a5574c2c54e18bd288299fee3a6751526b/global.json#L22)
```json
    "dotnet-api-docs_netcoreapp3.0": "0.0.0.1"
```

Issues.Title: [release/5.0-rc2] Remove WpfDllVerifier checks from WPF
Issues.Body:
Remove WpfDllVerifier checks from WPF #3322 

>WPF has runtime checks to verify the correct versions of WPF assemblies are being loaded. It does so by validating that the DLLs are loaded from the same path. These checks were very useful when porting WPF from .NET Framework to .NET Core, but WPF assembly load locations are varied for .NET 5 scenarios. The WpfDllVerifier class and uses of it should be removed for .NET 5.

The brings @agocke's change (https://github.com/dotnet/wpf/pull/3329) to release/5.0 from master.

Issue: https://github.com/dotnet/wpf/issues/3322
Issues.RelatedDescription: Closed or merged PR "[release/5.0-rc2] Remove WpfDllVerifier checks from WPF " (#3436)

Issues.Title: [release/5.0-rc2] Fix raw stylus data to support per-monitor DPI
Issues.Body:
## [release/5.0-rc2] Fix raw stylus data to support per-monitor DPI 

> Using the TouchMove event in a multi-dpi scenario, the interpolated points returned are not correctly adjusting for DPI, whereas the current point is.

This brings @rladuca's change from master to release/5.0. 

#### Original Issue:

TouchMove intermediate points are not DPI aware (https://github.com/dotnet/wpf/issues/2072)

#### Original PR:

Fix raw stylus data to support per-monitor DPI (https://github.com/dotnet/wpf/pull/2891)
